  </div>
  <div class="large-4 columns">
    <span class="phase-length">1-2 Weeks</span>
    <ul>
      <li>$2,500 flat fee</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="row project-delivery-phase">
  <div class="large-2 columns hide-for-small center-text">
    <span class="phase-word">Phase</span>
    <span class="phase-number">II</span>
  </div>
  <div class="large-6 columns">
    <h5 class="phase-title hide-for-small">Floor Plans and Planning Permits</h5>
    <h5 class="phase-title show-for-small">Phase II - Floor Plans and Planning Permits</h5>
    <p>One of our architects works with you to create floor plans (aka blueprints). You will get floor plans, site plans, furniture layouts. The project schedule and budget are updated accordingly if needed. All zoning forms will be completed and submitted.</p>
    <p><%= link_to "&raquo; See Sample Phase II Deliverable (PDF, 6.8 MB)".html_safe, "https://d30c147332eb2dec5310-0058d95ebdf51c2bd9f43fd0921533e4.ssl.cf1.rackcdn.com/static-assets/samples/Sample%20Phase%202%20Deliverable.pdf", :target => "_blank" %></p>
  </div>
  <div class="large-4 columns">
    <span class="phase-length">~1 month</span>
    <ul>
      <li>$2,000-$4,000 of architect time</li>
      <li>~$4,000 in city planning/zoning permit fees (average $4,000 but range from $150-$40,000 – fees are researched in Phase I)</li>
      <li>$1,500-$2,500 for site survey</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="row project-delivery-phase">
  <div class="large-2 columns hide-for-small center-text">
    <span class="phase-word">Phase</span>
    <span class="phase-number">III</span>
  </div>
  <div class="large-6 columns">
    <h5 class="phase-title hide-for-small">Design Details: Materials and Appliances</h5>
    <h5 class="phase-title show-for-small">Phase III - Design Details: Materials and Appliances</h5>
    <p>The Architect will work with you (meetings, emails, phone calls and visits to local stores) to create a detailed design. You will pick finish details such as appliances, floor type, siding material, window and door selections, roofing material, heating systems, tile and other material selections necessary to complete the home. The budget and schedule are updated accordingly.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="large-4 columns">
    <span class="phase-length">~1-2 months</span>
    <ul>
      <li>$2,000-$8,000+ of architect time (as much or as little time as you'd like)</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="row project-delivery-phase">
  <div class="large-2 columns hide-for-small center-text">
    <span class="phase-word">Phase</span>
    <span class="phase-number">IV</span>
  </div>
  <div class="large-6 columns">
    <h5 class="phase-title hide-for-small">Documentation and Building Permits</h5>
    <h5 class="phase-title show-for-small">Phase IV - Documentation and Building Permits</h5>
    <p>The architect prepares final construction documents, specifications and submittals for city building permits. By this phase, you will get plans that include as-built drawings, site plans, demolition plans, floor plans, cross-sections, engineering, interior and exterior elevations, and finish schedules. Structural engineering will be completed by a licensed engineer. You will receive your building permit now.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="large-4 columns">
    <span class="phase-length">~1 month</span>
    <ul>
      <li>$4,000-$7,000 of architect time and engineering as required. Engineering typically costs $4,000.</li>
      <li>~$3,000-$6,000 in building permit fees. </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>

